definition.value: A tripeptide composed of L-proline, L-glutamic acid and L-isoleucine joined in sequence by peptide linkages.
An amino dicarboxylic acid that is meso-2,6-diaminopimelic acid in which a hydrogen at position 3 has been replaced by a hydroxy group. It is a constituent of bacterial cell wall peptidoglycan.
A 2,6-diaminopimelic acid in which both chiral centres have R configuration.

An enoate ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of (2E)-4-{(2S,3R,4R,5S)-3,4-dihydroxy-5-[(2E,4R,5S)-5-hydroxy-4-methylhex-2-en-1-yl]oxan-2-yl}-3-methylbut-2-enoic acid with the alcoholic hydroxy group of 8-hydroxyoctanoic acid.
An  aryl sulfate oxoanion that is the conjugate base of indoxyl sulfate, obtained by deprotonation of the sulfo group; major species at pH 7.3.
